etymologies: mid 17th century: from Latin, ‘producer (of games), publisher’, from edit- ‘produced, put out’, from the verb edere

definitions: a person who is in charge of and determines the final content of a text, particularly a newspaper or magazine

examples.text: the editor of The New York Times

shortDefinitions: person who is in charge of and determines final content of newspaper

definitions: a person who works for a publishing company, commissioning or preparing material for publication.
shortDefinitions: person who commissions or prepares material for publication or broadcast

definitions: a computer program enabling the user to enter or alter text

examples.text: you will be able to use the editor to make any changes you want

shortDefinitions: computer program enabling user to enter or alter text
